ety's ethical values and to democratic political participation. Lying at the intersection of International Relations, American politics, terrorism studies, discourse analysis, communication studies and cultural studies, this book will have genuine interdisciplinary appeal.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMass media and language. 0aMass media and public opinion. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009xLanguage. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009xPublic opinion. 0aWar on Terrorism, 2001-2009. 4aPolitical Studies 2021. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2018. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Essays.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aPearl Harbor.  aWorld War II.  acatastrophic threat.  acounter-terrorism.  acritical discourse analysis.  anational identity.  apolitical narrative.  apublic language.  asocial actors.  awar on terrorism.1 aJackson, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613092140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526130921423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526130921/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles